children.subject:
1) CS 188 is p irrelevant to CS 189 in terms of actual material covered, so feel free to ignore it if you're taking it primarily/entirely because of 189 prep (which is of course not the only reason to take 188)

2) Taking 127 without 16B is fine. It'll be more work than if you'd taken 16B, but it's not the end of the world.

3) The workload you've suggested seems fine, but you'll probably get more out of all 3 classes if you take 100 first since in the areas where 100 overlaps with 189 and 127, it's a gentler and arguably more conceptual introduction to the material. I'd also suggest 127 before 189 if possible, but taking them together is fine too (and some people prefer it that way)

Hey everyone,

I am planning on taking CS 189 in Fall 2022, with whoever is teaching it then. By then, the relevant courses I would have taken to prepare me for that class would be EECS 16A, Math 54, Math 53, CS 70, EECS 126, and possibly CS 188. I would like to take EECS 127 alongside CS 189, but am apprehensive about taking EECS 127 without having taken EECS 16B. 

Will my preparation for CS 189 be sufficient, or is it strongly recommended that I avoid the class without having taken EECS 16? 

Furthermore, does a schedule for that semester consisting of something like CS 189, EECS 127, and Data C100 (and nothing else) seem reasonable? Or does that sound like it will be extremely overwhelming, especially if I am taking EECS 127 without having taken EECS 16B?

All input appreciated! Thank you :)
